message.content:
Sorry, the task given is impossible. Bytecode is the compiled version of a smart contract. It is not feasible to get the exact Solidity code from bytecode because the compilation process is a one-way operation. 

Bytecode doesn't hold variable names, comments, or the original formatting because all of these are not needed for the execution of the code, so they are lost during the compilation process.

If you have misplaced the original Solidity code, the best you can do is to decompile the bytecode to get the equivalent assembly code. However, this assembly code will be much harder to understand than the original Solidity code.
